Opening an existing review results in a NullPointerException.
SvnCache.java getFileRevision() (FeCru 2.5.3):
{code}
        int revid = fileRevDAO.getRevId(path, rev);
        SvnRevInfo revInfo = null;
        if (revid != -1) {
            revInfo = fileRevDAO.load(revid);
            String container = repositoryInfo.getPathMatcher().getContainerId(path);
            if (container.startsWith(SvnLogicalPathMatcher.TAG_ID) && !revInfo.getPath().equals(path)) {
                Path tagRoot = repositoryInfo.getPathMatcher().getTagRoot(path);
                int tagRootRevid = fileRevDAO.getRevId(tagRoot, rev);
                SvnRevInfo tagRev = fileRevDAO.load(tagRootRevid);
                revInfo.setSVNRevision(tagRev.getSvnRevision());
            }
        }
        return revInfo;
{code}
tagRev.getSvnRevision() fails as tagRev can be null.
revInfo.setSVNRevision() could also fail if revInfo is null, but is has been referenced in the if statement, so we know it's not null, and didn't cause this NPE.

